# GSD Git Workflow

## Mandatory Pre-Flight — runs BEFORE any code or planning

When the user asks to start or resume a phase, your **first response** must be this
checklist — printed and actioned before touching any file:

```
## Pre-Flight Checklist — Phase NN

- [ ] Branch:  git checkout -b feature/phase-NN-<slug>   (run this now)
- [ ] Spec:    .planning/phase-NN-SPEC.md exists and is committed
- [ ] Gate:    npm test && npx biome check .      (run before EVERY commit)
- [ ] No work on main directly
```

Do not write, plan, or scaffold any code until every item is checked.
If the spec file does not exist, create and commit it first.

---

## Branch per Phase

Before starting any phase of work, create a branch:

```bash
git checkout -b feature/phase-NN-<slug>   # e.g. feature/phase-01-foundation
```

- Use the phase number and a short kebab-case slug matching the ROADMAP phase name.
- Never implement on `main` directly.
- Merge the phase branch to `main` only after §8.3 Definition of Done is satisfied.

## Atomic Commits per Task

Commit after every discrete task — not after the whole phase:

```bash
# GOOD — one task, one commit
git commit -m "feat(01): add pipeline list screen with seeded leads"
git commit -m "feat(01): add lead profile card component"
git commit -m "test(01): assert initial load renders 10 leads"

# BAD — entire phase in one commit
git commit -m "done with phase 1"
```

### Commit message format

```
<type>(<phase>): <short description>
```

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `test`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`.

## Test + Lint Gate (per commit)

Run **before every commit**. Do not commit if either fails:

```bash
npm test && npx biome check .
```

This is per commit, not per phase. Running the gate only once per phase allowed
formatting drift and silent failures to accumulate across multiple commits.

If tests fail, fix before committing — never commit a broken state.

## Phase Completion

Before merging, verify all of the following (from TECHSPEC §8.3):

1. `.planning/phase-NN-SPEC.md` was committed before any implementation code.
2. `.planning/phase-NN-SUMMARY.md` exists on the phase branch (documenting what
   was built, decisions made, tests added, and known issues).
3. All applicable test cases from §1.3 are covered. For test-related phases,
   produce a **§1.3 case verification table** mapping each case to its test file
   and describe block. Any uncovered case blocks the merge.
4. `npm test && npx biome check .` passes.
5. STATE.md is updated to "Phase NN — Complete" with next task set.

Then merge:

```bash
git checkout main
git merge feature/phase-NN-<slug> --no-ff -m "merge(NN): complete <phase name>"
```
